It is evident, that Moses calleth the Lord the, Testament (greek 
                   in non-Latin alphabet 
               ) saying, behold I my Testament with thee; for before he said the Testament (or Covenant) was not to be sought in the Scripture: again he saith in the preaching of Peter, thou shalt find the Lord called the Law, and the Word or Reason.

XXVIII. Again, Origin lib. 1. contra Celsum, saith, The simple (or perfect) words of Sacred Scripture have made the sincere Readers of it to be Enthusiastically moved (gr. 
                   in non-Latin alphabet 
               ) who nourish that light with the Oyl which the five Virgins are said to have in their Lamps, as in the Parable.
